This paper deals with the application of deep learning models for anomaly detection and segmentation in medical images, specifically brain MR images. The paper discusses the use of autoencoders and GANs for this purpose, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.NE) and specifically brain MR images (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
